The paper deals with signal recovery from Fourier measurements, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of symmetrization and zero-padding is a technique often used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) for image processing and feature extraction. Finally, the paper also involves optimization techniques for recovery, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
